5000|$|At the Heart of Winter {{was well}} {{received}} by critics. John Serba of Allmusic praised the album, writing, [...] "the {{result is a}} clarity and focus that few purveyors of the genre succeeded at finding, a painstakingly organized assemblage of <b>black</b> <b>metal's</b> base elements into a disciplined purity of metal that prefers {{the power of the}} almighty riff, instead of the occasionally overblown classical structuring of much-lauded stalwarts Emperor and Cradle of Filth, or the strange experimentation that Mayhem and Arcturus would undertake".|$|R
